Access Azure DocumentDB resources from php!

Usage :

include 'documentdb-for-php.php';

$host = 'https://yourdocumentdbaccount.documents.azure.com';
$master_key = 'yourmasterkey==';
$db = 'yourdbname';
$db_rid = 'thedbresourceid==';
$coll = 'yourcollectionname';
$coll_rid = 'yourcollectionresourceid=';
$query = "Select * from ..."; // your sql :)

querycoll($host, $db_rid, $coll_rid, $query,$apptype,$useragent,$cachecontrol,$da_date,$api_version,$master,$token,$master_key,$da_date);

You will get back a json response with whatever you asked in the query, that simple!

currently tested for select statements